<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="correct-adj">correct <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kə'rekt/    美 /kə'rekt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-right">1.★ <strong>正确的；无误的(right)</strong></h4>
<p>反 incorrect </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everyone gives a different answer, but everyone is correct. 
每个人的答案都不相同，但是大家都是正确的。</p><footer>2010 江苏</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>恰当的；正当的</strong></h4>
<p>suitable：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Only if you eat the correct foods will you be able to keep fit and stay healthy.
只有恰当饮食，才能保持身体健康。</p><footer>2008 江苏</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>得体的；合乎礼节的</strong></h4>
<p>formal and polite
反 incorrect ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>correct behaviour</strong>
得体的行为</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s not correct to speak like that.
那样说话不妥。</p></div></div>